#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:12.5"
msgid "2. Ariyaaṭṭhaṅgikamagga"
msgstr "2. The Noble Eightfold Path"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: dakkhati → dakkhiti (bj) | dākkhīti (pts1)
msgctxt "dn8:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atthi, kassapa, maggo atthi paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva ñassati sāmaṃ "
"dakkhati:"
msgstr ""
"There is, Kassapa, a path, there is a practice, practicing in accordance "
"with which you will know and see for yourself:"

# Note the va, which is ignored by RD and MW. Comm, however, takes it in exclusive sense, referring back to the Brahmajala. The usage is similar to, eg. eso’va maggo, natthi anno, and, given the context, it seems likely this exclusive sense was meant here.
msgctxt "dn8:13.2"
msgid "‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Only the ascetic Gotama’s words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line "
"with the teaching and training.’"

msgctxt "dn8:13.3"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca, kassapa, maggo, katamā ca paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva "
"ñassati sāmaṃ dakkhati:"
msgstr "And what is that path?"

msgctxt "dn8:13.4"
msgid "‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:13.5"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "dn8:13.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo "
"sammāvāyāmo sammāsati sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "dn8:13.7"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, kassapa, maggo, ayaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva ñassati "
"sāmaṃ dakkhati ‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī "
"vinayavādī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is the path, this is the practice, practicing in accordance with which "
"you will know and see for yourself: ‘Only the ascetic Gotama’s words are "
"timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:13.8"
msgid "3. Tapopakkamakathā"
msgstr "3. Practicing Self-Mortification"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.166"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:14.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Kassapa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn8:14.2"
msgid ""
"“imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Gotama, those ascetics and brahmins consider these practices of "
"self-mortification to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:14.3"
msgid ""
"Acelako hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano, naehibhaddantiko, "
"natiṭṭhabhaddantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ, na uddissakataṃ, na nimantanaṃ sādiyati."
msgstr ""
"They go naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come "
"or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food "
"prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal."

msgctxt "dn8:14.4"
msgid ""
"So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na "
"eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ "
"bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na "
"saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā "
"saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ, na maṃsaṃ, na suraṃ, na merayaṃ, na thusodakaṃ "
"pivati."
msgstr ""
"They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps "
"sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is "
"eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has "
"a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They "
"accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer."

msgctxt "dn8:14.5"
msgid ""
"So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … sattāgāriko vā "
"hoti sattālopiko;"
msgstr ""
"They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses "
"and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls."

msgctxt "dn8:14.6"
msgid ""
"ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti;"
msgstr ""
"They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day."

msgctxt "dn8:14.7"
msgid ""
"ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ "
"āhāreti. Iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, "
"even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating "
"food at set intervals."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:14.8"
msgid ""
"Imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins also consider these practices of self-"
"mortification to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:14.9"
msgid ""
"Sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, "
"daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, "
"ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, "
"gomayabhakkho vā hoti, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr ""
"They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum "
"from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest "
"roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.167"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:14.10"
msgid ""
"Imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins also consider these practices of mortification "
"to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin."

# vekaṭikopi hoti vikaṭabhojanānuyogamanuyutto means eating urine, etc. see MN 12.
msgctxt "dn8:14.11"
msgid ""
"Sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi "
"dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, "
"kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, "
"kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhikampi dhāreti, "
msgstr ""
"They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh "
"tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, "
"human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.12"
msgid "kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They tear out hair and beard, committed to this practice. "

#. VAR: ubbhaṭṭhakopi → ubbhaṭṭhikopi (mr)
msgctxt "dn8:14.13"
msgid "ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanapaṭikkhitto, "
msgstr "They constantly stand, refusing seats. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.14"
msgid "ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.15"
msgid "kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti, "
msgstr "They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.16"
msgid "phalakaseyyampi kappeti, thaṇḍilaseyyampi kappeti, "
msgstr "They make their bed on a plank, or the bare ground. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.17"
msgid "ekapassayikopi hoti "
msgstr "They lie only on one side. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.18"
msgid "rajojalladharo, "
msgstr "They wear dust and dirt. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.19"
msgid "abbhokāsikopi hoti "
msgstr "They stay in the open air. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.20"
msgid "yathāsanthatiko, "
msgstr "They sleep wherever they lay their mat. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.21"
msgid "vekaṭikopi hoti vikaṭabhojanānuyogamanuyutto, "
msgstr ""
"They eat unnatural things, committed to the practice of eating unnatural "
"foods. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.22"
msgid "apānakopi hoti apānakattamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They don’t drink, committed to the practice of not drinking liquids. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.23"
msgid "sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They’re committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, "
"including the evening.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:14.24"
msgid "4. Tapopakkamaniratthakathā"
msgstr "4. The Uselessness of Self-Mortification"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Acelako cepi, kassapa, hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ "
"addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr "“Kassapa, someone may practice all those forms of self-mortification,"

msgctxt "dn8:15.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa cāyaṃ sīlasampadā cittasampadā paññāsampadā abhāvitā hoti asacchikatā. "
"Atha kho so ārakāva sāmaññā ārakāva brahmaññā."
msgstr ""
"but if they haven’t developed and realized any accomplishment in ethics, "
"mind, and wisdom, they are far from being a true ascetic or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:15.3"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"But take a mendicant who develops a heart of love, free of enmity and ill "
"will. And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn8:15.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""
"When they achieve this, they’re called a mendicant who is a ‘true ascetic’ "
"and also ‘a true brahmin’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.168"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:15.5"
msgid ""
"Sākabhakkho cepi, kassapa, hoti, sāmākabhakkho … pe … vanamūlaphalāhāro "
"yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa cāyaṃ sīlasampadā cittasampadā paññāsampadā abhāvitā hoti asacchikatā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.7"
msgid "Atha kho so ārakāva sāmaññā ārakāva brahmaññā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.8"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:15.10"
msgid "Sāṇāni cepi, kassapa, dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.11"
msgid "sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.12"
msgid ""
"Tassa cāyaṃ sīlasampadā cittasampadā paññāsampadā abhāvitā hoti asacchikatā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.13"
msgid "Atha kho so ārakāva sāmaññā ārakāva brahmaññā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.14"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:15.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Kassapa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn8:16.2"
msgid "“dukkaraṃ, bho gotama, sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan”ti."
msgstr "“It’s hard, Master Gotama, to be a true ascetic or a true brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn8:16.3"
msgid ""
"“Pakati kho esā, kassapa, lokasmiṃ ‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s typical, Kassapa, in this world to think that it’s hard to be a true "
"ascetic or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:16.4"
msgid ""
"Acelako cepi, kassapa, hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ "
"addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr "But someone might practice all those forms of self-mortification."

msgctxt "dn8:16.5"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena sāmaññaṃ vā abhavissa "
"brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"And if it was only because of just that much, only because of that self-"
"mortification that it was so very hard to be a true ascetic or brahmin, it "
"wouldn’t be appropriate to say that"

msgctxt "dn8:16.6"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr "it’s hard to be a true ascetic or brahmin."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.7"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca panetaṃ abhavissa kātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""
"For it would be quite possible for a householder or a householder’s child—or "
"even the bonded maid who carries the water-jar—"

msgctxt "dn8:16.8"
msgid ""
"‘handāhaṃ acelako homi, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ "
"addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "to practice all those forms of self-mortification."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.169"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.9"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"sāmaññaṃ vā hoti brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"It’s because there’s something other than just that much, something other "
"than that self-mortification that it’s so very hard to be a true ascetic or "
"brahmin. And that’s why it is appropriate to say that"

msgctxt "dn8:16.10"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr "it’s hard to be a true ascetic or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:16.11"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who develops a heart of love, free of enmity and ill will. "
"And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn8:16.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""
"When they achieve this, they’re called a mendicant who is a ‘true ascetic’ "
"and also ‘a true brahmin’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.13"
msgid ""
"Sākabhakkho cepi, kassapa, hoti, sāmākabhakkho … pe … vanamūlaphalāhāro "
"yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.14"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena sāmaññaṃ vā abhavissa "
"brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.15"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.16"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca panetaṃ abhavissa kātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.17"
msgid ""
"‘handāhaṃ sākabhakkho vā homi, sāmākabhakkho vā … pe … vanamūlaphalāhāro "
"yāpemi pavattaphalabhojī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.18"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"sāmaññaṃ vā hoti brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.19"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.20"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.22"
msgid ""
"Sāṇāni cepi, kassapa, dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti … pe … sāyatatiyakampi "
"udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.23"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena sāmaññaṃ vā abhavissa "
"brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.24"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.25"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca panetaṃ abhavissa kātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.26"
msgid ""
"‘handāhaṃ sāṇānipi dhāremi, masāṇānipi dhāremi … pe … sāyatatiyakampi "
"udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:16.27"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"sāmaññaṃ vā hoti brahmaññaṃ vā dukkaraṃ sudukkaraṃ, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ "
"vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.28"
msgid "‘dukkaraṃ sāmaññaṃ dukkaraṃ brahmaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.29"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:16.30"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.170"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Kassapa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn8:17.2"
msgid "“dujjāno, bho gotama, samaṇo, dujjāno brāhmaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“It’s hard, Master Gotama, to know a true ascetic or a true brahmin.”"

msgctxt "dn8:17.3"
msgid "“Pakati kho esā, kassapa, lokasmiṃ ‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s typical in this world to think that it’s hard to know a true ascetic "
"or brahmin."

msgctxt "dn8:17.4"
msgid ""
"Acelako cepi, kassapa, hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ "
"addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr "But someone might practice all those forms of self-mortification."

msgctxt "dn8:17.5"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena samaṇo vā abhavissa brāhmaṇo "
"vā dujjāno sudujjāno, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"And if it was only by just that much, only by that self-mortification that "
"it was so very hard to know a true ascetic or brahmin, it wouldn’t be "
"appropriate to say that"

msgctxt "dn8:17.6"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr "it’s hard to know a true ascetic or brahmin."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.7"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca paneso abhavissa ñātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""
"For it would be quite possible for a householder or a householder’s child—or "
"even the bonded maid who carries the water-jar—"

msgctxt "dn8:17.8"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ acelako hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ "
"addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"to know that someone is practicing all those forms of self-mortification."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.9"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"samaṇo vā hoti brāhmaṇo vā dujjāno sudujjāno, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"It’s because there’s something other than just that much, something other "
"than that self-mortification that it’s so very hard to know a true ascetic "
"or brahmin. And that’s why it is appropriate to say that"

msgctxt "dn8:17.10"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr "it’s hard to know a true ascetic or brahmin."

#. VAR: Yato kho → yato ca kho (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn8:17.11"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who develops a heart of love, free of enmity and ill will. "
"And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn8:17.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""
"When they achieve this, they’re called a mendicant who is a ‘true ascetic’ "
"and also ‘a true brahmin’.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.13"
msgid ""
"Sākabhakkho cepi, kassapa, hoti sāmākabhakkho … pe … vanamūlaphalāhāro "
"yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.14"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena samaṇo vā abhavissa brāhmaṇo "
"vā dujjāno sudujjāno, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.15"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.16"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca paneso abhavissa ñātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.17"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ sākabhakkho vā hoti sāmākabhakkho … pe … vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti "
"pavattaphalabhojī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.171"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.18"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"samaṇo vā hoti brāhmaṇo vā dujjāno sudujjāno, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.19"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.20"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.22"
msgid ""
"Sāṇāni cepi, kassapa, dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti … pe … sāyatatiyakampi "
"udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.23"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, mattāya iminā tapopakkamena samaṇo vā abhavissa brāhmaṇo "
"vā dujjāno sudujjāno, netaṃ abhavissa kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.24"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.25"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca paneso abhavissa ñātuṃ gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā antamaso "
"kumbhadāsiyāpi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.26"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti … pe … sāyatatiyakampi "
"udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharatī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:17.27"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, kassapa, aññatreva imāya mattāya aññatra iminā tapopakkamena "
"samaṇo vā hoti brāhmaṇo vā dujjāno sudujjāno, tasmā etaṃ kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.28"
msgid "‘dujjāno samaṇo dujjāno brāhmaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.29"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca "
"khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:17.30"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:17.31"
msgid "5. Sīlasamādhipaññāsampadā"
msgstr "5. The Accomplishment of Ethics, Immersion, and Wisdom"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:18.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Kassapa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn8:18.2"
msgid ""
"“katamā pana sā, bho gotama, sīlasampadā, katamā cittasampadā, katamā "
"paññāsampadā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Master Gotama, what is that accomplishment in ethics, in mind, and in "
"wisdom?”"

msgctxt "dn8:18.3"
msgid "“Idha, kassapa, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ, sammāsambuddho … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened "
"Buddha …"

msgctxt "dn8:18.4"
msgid ""
"bhayadassāvī samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu, kāyakammavacīkammena "
"samannāgato kusalena parisuddhājīvo sīlasampanno indriyesu guttadvāro "
"satisampajaññena samannāgato santuṭṭho."
msgstr ""
"Seeing danger in the slightest flaw, a mendicant keeps the rules they’ve "
"undertaken. They act skillfully by body and speech. They’re purified in "
"livelihood and accomplished in ethical conduct. They guard the sense doors, "
"have mindfulness and situational awareness, and are content."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.172"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:18.5"
msgid "Kathañca, kassapa, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant accomplished in ethics?"

msgctxt "dn8:18.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, kassapa, bhikkhu pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti "
"nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the "
"rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion "
"for all living beings."

msgctxt "dn8:18.7"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasampadāya … pe …"
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in ethics. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:19.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood. …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ … pe … osadhīnaṃ patimokkho"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn8:19.3"
msgid "iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"They refrain from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn8:19.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.173"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
#. VAR: Sa kho so → ayaṃ kho (mr)
msgctxt "dn8:19.5"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, kassapa, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ "
"samanupassati, yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in any quarter in "
"regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn8:19.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, kassapa, rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto nihatapaccāmitto na kutoci "
"bhayaṃ samanupassati, yadidaṃ paccatthikato;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a king who has defeated his enemies. He sees no danger from his "
"foes in any quarter."

msgctxt "dn8:19.7"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, kassapa, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ "
"samanupassati, yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in "
"any quarter in regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn8:19.8"
msgid ""
"So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a "
"blameless happiness inside themselves."

msgctxt "dn8:19.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, kassapa, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics."

msgctxt "dn8:19.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, kassapa, sīlasampadā … pe …"
msgstr "This, Kassapa, is that accomplishment in ethics. …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.11"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.12"
msgid "Idampissa hoti cittasampadāya … pe …"
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in mind. …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.13"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "They enter and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.14"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn8:19.15"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "dn8:19.16"
msgid "Idampissa hoti cittasampadāya."
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in mind."

msgctxt "dn8:19.17"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, kassapa, cittasampadā."
msgstr "This, Kassapa, is that accomplishment in mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs20"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.174"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:20.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte … pe …"
msgstr "When their mind is immersed like this,"

msgctxt "dn8:20.2"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti …"
msgstr "they extend and project it toward knowledge and vision …"

msgctxt "dn8:20.3"
msgid "idampissa hoti paññāsampadāya … pe …"
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in wisdom. …"

msgctxt "dn8:20.4"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn8:20.5"
msgid "Idampissa hoti paññāsampadāya."
msgstr "This pertains to their accomplishment in wisdom."

msgctxt "dn8:20.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, kassapa, paññāsampadā."
msgstr "This, Kassapa, is that accomplishment in wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:20.7"
msgid ""
"Imāya ca, kassapa, sīlasampadāya cittasampadāya paññāsampadāya aññā "
"sīlasampadā cittasampadā paññāsampadā uttaritarā vā paṇītatarā vā natthi."
msgstr ""
"And, Kassapa, there is no accomplishment in ethics, mind, and wisdom that is "
"better or finer than this."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:20.8"
msgid "6. Sīhanādakathā"
msgstr "6. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:21.1"
msgid "Santi, kassapa, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sīlavādā."
msgstr "There are, Kassapa, some ascetics and brahmins who teach ethics."

msgctxt "dn8:21.2"
msgid "Te anekapariyāyena sīlassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr "They praise ethical conduct in many ways."

msgctxt "dn8:21.3"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, kassapa, ariyaṃ paramaṃ sīlaṃ, nāhaṃ tattha attano samasamaṃ "
"samanupassāmi, kuto bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"But as far as the highest noble ethics goes, I don’t see anyone who’s my "
"equal, still less my superior."

msgctxt "dn8:21.4"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo, yadidaṃ adhisīlaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:21.5"
msgid "Santi, kassapa, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā tapojigucchāvādā."
msgstr ""
"There are, Kassapa, some ascetics and brahmins who teach mortification in "
"disgust of sin."

msgctxt "dn8:21.6"
msgid "Te anekapariyāyena tapojigucchāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr "They praise mortification in disgust of sin in many ways."

msgctxt "dn8:21.7"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, kassapa, ariyā paramā tapojigucchā, nāhaṃ tattha attano samasamaṃ "
"samanupassāmi, kuto bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"But as far as the highest noble mortification in disgust of sin goes, I don’"
"t see anyone who’s my equal, still less my superior."

msgctxt "dn8:21.8"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo, yadidaṃ adhijegucchaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher "
"mortification in disgust of sin."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:21.9"
msgid "Santi, kassapa, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā paññāvādā."
msgstr "There are, Kassapa, some ascetics and brahmins who teach wisdom."

msgctxt "dn8:21.10"
msgid "Te anekapariyāyena paññāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr "They praise wisdom in many ways."

msgctxt "dn8:21.11"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, kassapa, ariyā paramā paññā, nāhaṃ tattha attano samasamaṃ "
"samanupassāmi, kuto bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"But as far as the highest noble wisdom goes, I don’t see anyone who’s my "
"equal, still less my superior."

msgctxt "dn8:21.12"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo, yadidaṃ adhipaññaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:21.13"
msgid "Santi, kassapa, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā vimuttivādā."
msgstr "There are, Kassapa, some ascetics and brahmins who teach freedom."

msgctxt "dn8:21.14"
msgid "Te anekapariyāyena vimuttiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr "They praise freedom in many ways."

msgctxt "dn8:21.15"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, kassapa, ariyā paramā vimutti, nāhaṃ tattha attano samasamaṃ "
"samanupassāmi, kuto bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"But as far as the highest noble freedom goes, I don’t see anyone who’s my "
"equal, still less my superior."

msgctxt "dn8:21.16"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo, yadidaṃ adhivimutti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs22"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.175"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:22.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, kassapa, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn8:22.2"
msgid ""
"‘sīhanādaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo nadati, tañca kho suññāgāre nadati, no "
"parisāsū’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama only roars his lion’s roar in an empty hut, not in an "
"assembly.’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.3"
msgid "Te: ‘mā hevan’tissu vacanīyā."
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so!’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.4"
msgid ""
"‘Sīhanādañca samaṇo gotamo nadati, parisāsu ca nadatī’ti evamassu, kassapa, "
"vacanīyā."
msgstr ""
"What should be said is this: ‘The ascetic Gotama roars his lion’s roar, and "
"he roars it in an assembly.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:22.5"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, kassapa, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn8:22.6"
msgid ""
"‘sīhanādañca samaṇo gotamo nadati, parisāsu ca nadati, no ca kho visārado "
"nadatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama roars his lion’s roar, and he roars it in an assembly. "
"But he doesn’t roar it boldly.’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.7"
msgid "Te: ‘mā hevan’tissu vacanīyā."
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so!’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.8"
msgid ""
"‘Sīhanādañca samaṇo gotamo nadati, parisāsu ca nadati, visārado ca nadatī’ti "
"evamassu, kassapa, vacanīyā."
msgstr ""
"What should be said is this: ‘The ascetic Gotama roars his lion’s roar, he "
"roars it in an assembly, and he roars it boldly.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:22.9"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, kassapa, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn8:22.10"
msgid ""
"‘sīhanādañca samaṇo gotamo nadati, parisāsu ca nadati, visārado ca nadati, "
"no ca kho naṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama roars his lion’s roar, he roars it in an assembly, and "
"he roars it boldly. But they don’t question him. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.11"
msgid "pañhañca naṃ pucchanti; no ca kho nesaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti … pe …"
msgstr "Or he doesn’t answer their questions. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.12"
msgid ""
"pañhañca nesaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti; no ca kho pañhassa veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ "
"ārādheti … pe …"
msgstr "Or his answers are not satisfactory. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.13"
msgid ""
"pañhassa ca veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheti; no ca kho sotabbaṃ maññanti … pe …"
msgstr "Or they don’t think him worth listening to. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.14"
msgid "sotabbañcassa maññanti; no ca kho sutvā pasīdanti … pe …"
msgstr "Or they’re not confident after listening. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.15"
msgid "sutvā cassa pasīdanti; no ca kho pasannākāraṃ karonti … pe …"
msgstr "Or they don’t show their confidence. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.16"
msgid "pasannākārañca karonti; no ca kho tathattāya paṭipajjanti … pe …"
msgstr "Or they don’t practice accordingly. …"

msgctxt "dn8:22.17"
msgid "tathattāya ca paṭipajjanti; no ca kho paṭipannā ārādhentī’ti."
msgstr "Or they don’t succeed in their practice.’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.18"
msgid "Te: ‘mā hevan’tissu vacanīyā."
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so!’"

msgctxt "dn8:22.19"
msgid ""
"‘Sīhanādañca samaṇo gotamo nadati, parisāsu ca nadati, visārado ca nadati, "
"pañhañca naṃ pucchanti, pañhañca nesaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti, pañhassa ca "
"veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheti, sotabbañcassa maññanti, sutvā cassa "
"pasīdanti, pasannākārañca karonti, tathattāya ca paṭipajjanti, paṭipannā ca "
"ārādhentī’ti evamassu, kassapa, vacanīyā."
msgstr ""
"What should be said is this: ‘The ascetic Gotama roars his lion’s roar; he "
"roars it in an assembly; he roars it boldly; they question him; he answers "
"their questions; his answers are satisfactory; they think him worth "
"listening to; they’re confident after listening; they show their confidence; "
"they practice accordingly; and they succeed in their practice.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:22.20"
msgid "7. Titthiyaparivāsakathā"
msgstr "7. The Probation For One Previously Ordained"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs23"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.176"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:23.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, kassapa, samayaṃ rājagahe viharāmi gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"Kassapa, this one time I was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "dn8:23.2"
msgid ""
"Tatra maṃ aññataro tapabrahmacārī nigrodho nāma adhijegucche pañhaṃ apucchi."
msgstr ""
"There a certain practitioner of self-mortification named Nigrodha asked me "
"about the higher mortification in disgust of sin."

msgctxt "dn8:23.3"
msgid "Tassāhaṃ adhijegucche pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākāsiṃ."
msgstr "I answered his question."

msgctxt "dn8:23.4"
msgid "Byākate ca pana me attamano ahosi paraṃ viya mattāyā”ti."
msgstr "He was extremely happy with my answer.”"

msgctxt "dn8:23.5"
msgid ""
"“Ko hi, bhante, bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā na attamano assa paraṃ viya mattāya?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, who wouldn’t be extremely happy after hearing the Buddha’s teaching?"

msgctxt "dn8:23.6"
msgid "Ahampi hi, bhante, bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā attamano paraṃ viya mattāya."
msgstr "For I too am extremely happy after hearing the Buddha’s teaching!"

msgctxt "dn8:23.7"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn8:23.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo "
"pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in "
"many ways."

msgctxt "dn8:23.9"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn8:23.10"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:24.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo kho, kassapa, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati "
"pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati, catunnaṃ "
"māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti, upasampādenti "
"bhikkhubhāvāya."
msgstr ""
"“Kassapa, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the "
"going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend "
"four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants "
"are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood."

msgctxt "dn8:24.2"
msgid "Api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti."
msgstr "However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”"

msgctxt "dn8:24.3"
msgid ""
"“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhanti pabbajjaṃ, "
"ākaṅkhanti upasampadaṃ, cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena "
"āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti, upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya. Ahaṃ cattāri "
"vassāni parivasissāmi, catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū "
"pabbājentu, upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four "
"years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are "
"satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.177"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc54"></a>
msgctxt "dn8:24.4"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho acelo kassapo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the naked ascetic Kassapa received the going forth, the ordination in "
"the Buddha’s presence."

msgctxt "dn8:24.5"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā kassapo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharanto na cirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, Venerable Kassapa, living alone, withdrawn, "
"diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual "
"path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the "
"goal for which people from good families rightly go forth from the lay life "
"to homelessness."

msgctxt "dn8:24.6"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "dn8:24.7"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā kassapo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Kassapa became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn8:24.8"
msgid "Mahāsīhanādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
